# What I actually did

## Tessellate Payments - Staff Backend Engineer (2021 to present)
- Re-architected the authorization pipeline around an append-only ledger,
  removing a class of double-charge bugs that had caused 30+ incidents a year.
- Drove p99 latency from 840 ms to 120 ms by replacing a synchronous fraud
  check with a speculative-execution pattern and a 50 ms budget.
- Led the on-call rotation for 14 engineers; cut paging volume 60 percent by
  killing flappy alerts and adding SLO-based alerting.

## Northwind Logistics - Senior Engineer (2017 to 2021)
- Built the route-optimization service handling 2 million shipments a day.
- Migrated a 400-table monolith to a set of bounded services with zero downtime.

## Bluefin Mobile - Engineer (2014 to 2017)
- Owned the push-notification fan-out service (peak 1.2 million sends per minute).

